import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
sns.set()
WAW = pd.read_csv('WAW.csv', index_col=None) # WAW LAT 7.36201 and LONG 3.84850663.
WAW.set_index(['DAY'], inplace=True)
WAW.index.names = ['DAY']
WAW.columns.names = ['TIME']
WAW.plot()
plt.annotate('The time(6-9pm)with the lowest\n Concentration of Carbon monoxide',
xy=(6,51), xytext=(2,54), arrowprops=dict(facecolor='black',shrink=0.05));
plt.annotate('The time(12-3pm)with the highest \n Concentration of Carbon monoxide',
xy=(5,375), xytext=(2,330), arrowprops=dict(facecolor='red',shrink=0.05))
plt.title('CARBON MONOXIDE CONCENTRATION AT WAW ON \n 18TH – 24TH NOV, 2019 WITH LAT 7.36201 and LONG 3.84850663')
plt.ylabel('CARBON MONOXIDE CONCENTRATION')
plt.show()
